@node Usage
How to use
~~~~~~~~~~
ViewTGA can be started from Workbench or Shell. If You start it from a
shell the below listed arguments are allowed. Type 'ViewTGA ?' and all
available arguments are shown:


    FILENAME/M,W=WAIT/K/N,M=MODEID/K/N,R=SCREENREQ/S,V=VERBOSE/S:

    @{" FILENAME  " link FILENAME}

    @{" WAIT      " link WAIT}

    @{" MODEID    " link MODEID}

    @{" SCREENREQ " link SCREENREQ}

    @{" VERBOSE   " link VERBOSE}

If ViewTGA is started from  Workbench,  You  can  set  values  to  the
tooltypes  'WAIT', 'MODEID', 'SCREENREQ' and 'VERBOSE', which have the
same meaning as they have in shellstart.

Pressing a key or a mousebutton will  close  the  screen  and  ViewTGA
fetches  the  next  file  (in  Pattern  Matching  mode) or pops up the
filerequester again. Press the <ESC> key or  select  'Cancel'  in  the
file/screenrequest to abort the program.
@endnode

@node FILENAME
FILENAME:

      Simply the name of the picture you want to see. If  no  filename
      is   entered,   a   filerequester  will  appear.  AmigaDos-style
      pattern-matching is also supported.
@endnode

@node WAIT
WAIT:

      This is the optional duration time in seconds, an image will  be
      displayed. Useful for slideshows.
@endnode

@node MODEID
MODEID:

      If You want to force the image display screen to a specific  ID,
      You  have to set a vailid ScreenModeID for an Picasso 8/15/16/24
      Bit screen. The ID has to be for an 15-,16- or 24Bit  screen  if
      the  image  is a directcolor file and for an 8 Bit screen if the
      image  is  a  colormapped  file.  Look  out  for   the   utility
      'VScreenID'  which  helps  getting  the IDs. If You choose an ID
      which nominal sizes are smaller than  the  picture,  the  Screen
      will  be  an  auto  scrolling  one  if possible. If the pictures
      dimensions are too big to display, it will be  cropped.  If  the
      pictures  dimensions  are  smaller  than the screens, it will be
      displayed centered.
@endnode

@node SCREENREQ
SCREENREQ:

      ViewTGA tries to find a suitable screenmode by  itself.  If  You
      don't  like  that  screenmode,  the switch SCREENREQ will induce
      ViewTGA to open a screenmode requester where You can select Your
      favourite VillageScreen.
@endnode

@node VERBOSE
VERBOSE:

      By default no messages are printed out, even  errormessages  are
      disabled.  If  You  set  VERBOSE,  You will get some information
      about the image, screen etc.
@endnode


@node Requirement
Requirements
~~~~~~~~~~~~
   - An Amiga Computer with a UNSEGMENTED driven PICASSO II pluged in
   - 'vilintuisup.library' V2.x+
   - Amiga OS2.04+
@endnode

@node Notes
Notes
~~~~~
   - has not been tested on 1BM PICASSOs
   - has not been tested with interleaved images
@endnode

